The Bombay Stock Exchange was established in 1875.
Around 6,000 Indian companies list on the stock exchange, and it has a significant trading volume.
The index took only 10 trading days to gain 1,000 points after the index crossed the 19,000-mark on October 15. The major drivers of today's rally were index heavyweights Larsen and Toubro, Reliance Industries, ICICI Bank, HDFC Bank and SBI among others.
